---------------------------------------------
NETWORKMANAGER COMMAND LINE INTERFACE (nmcli)
---------------------------------------------

* Turn on wifi

nmcli radio wifi on


* Turn off wifi

nmcli radio wifi off


* Check wifi Status

nmcli radio wifi
 

* list all available wifi

nmcli dev wifi list


* to connect one of that wifi

nmcli dev wifi connect "SSID_NAME" password "YOUR_PASSWORD"


* to check status of connected wifi

nmcli connection show --active


* Set-up auto connect

nmcli connection modify "SSID_NAME" connection.autoconnect yes


* List All Saved Wi-Fi Networks

nmcli connection show


* Show the Password for a Specific Wi-Fi Network

/etc/NetworkManager/system-connections/

remember to use sudo to open file whichever you pick


